House Resolution 864
By: Representative Cheokas of the 151st
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring Melissa Montgomery; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Melissa Montgomery was the long time personal assistant to First Lady
3 Rosalynn Carter; and
4 WHEREAS, she was instrumental in the creation of the Rosalynn Carter Butterfly Trail
5 through partnerships with Emory University's deRoode Monarch Lab and Research,
6 Monarchs Across Georgia, and the United States Fish and Wildlife Services; and
7 WHEREAS, the Rosalynn Carter Butterfly Trail began due to Rosalynn Carter's concern of
8 the declining number of Monarch butterflies; and
9 WHEREAS, in 2013, Rosalynn decided she wanted to include native plants that would
10 provide habitat for Monarchs and other butterflies and pollinators in her private garden in
11 Plains as a way to help Monarchs; and
12 WHEREAS, this private garden was the beginning for the Rosalynn Carter Butterfly Trail,
13 which now has over 3,000 registered gardens across the United States; and
