14 WHEREAS, the success of the trail is due to supporters like Melissa Montgomery, Mrs.
15 Carter's personal assistant, who for over 39 years coordinated the personal, family, business,
16 and organizational details that Mrs. Carter was involved in; and
17 WHEREAS, due to Melissa's commitment to Mrs. Carter's desire to help the Monarchs, the
18 United States Fish and Wildlife Services entered into a partnership with the Rosalynn Carter
19 Butterfly Trail assisting with establishing funding and resources for hundreds of butterfly
20 gardens in public places and schools in the Southeastern United States; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this outstanding Georgian be
22 appropriately recognized.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body honor the contributions Melissa Montgomery has made to the
25 Rosalynn Carter Butterfly Trail.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
27 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
28 Melissa Montgomery.
